==Galician==
===Etymology===
From Old Galician and {{inh|gl|roa-opt|genrro||son-in-law}} (13th century, ''{{w|Cantigas de Santa Maria}}''), from {{inh|gl|la|gener|gener, generum|son-in-law}}, from {{inh|gl|ine-pro|*ǵm̥ros}}, from {{der|gl|ine-pro|*ǵem-}}. Cognate with {{cog|pt|genro}}, {{cog|es|yerno}}.
